---
import ShibuiContent from '../components/shibui/ShibuiContent.astro';
import ShibuiTerm from '../components/shibui/ShibuiTerm.astro';
import SketchContainer from '../components/sketches/SketchContainer.astro';
import { mappings } from '../data/ontology.json';
import vitals from '../data/vitals.json';
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { base } from '../utils/paths';

const wordsK = Math.floor(vitals.logos.words / 1000);
---

<Layout title="The Logocentric Architect — Philosophy" description="Bridging the gap between Humanities and Systems Engineering. How MFA-level rhetoric becomes production-grade code." shibuiFloor="standard">
  <div class="philosophy-page">
    <div class="sketch-accent">
      <SketchContainer sketchId="recursive-tree" height="300px" mobileHeight="200px" ariaLabel="Generative recursive tree representing the growth of ideas into systems" />
    </div>

    <article class="container container--narrow">
      <header class="philosophy-header" data-reveal>
        <h1 class="page-title">Rhetoric as System Design</h1>
        <p class="philosophy-subtitle">The Core Thesis of Anthony James Padavano</p>
      </header>

      <section class="prose" data-reveal style="--stagger-index: 1">
        <ShibuiContent id="philosophy.thesis.p1">
          <span slot="entry">
            <p>I came to engineering through literature and storytelling, not through computer science. For me, code is a medium for expressing ideas with precision — the same way an essay or a novel is.</p>
          </span>
          <span slot="elevated">
            <p>
              I do not come to engineering from a vacuum. I come to it from <strong>Literature</strong>, <strong>Rhetoric</strong>, and <strong><ShibuiTerm term="Narrative Theory" definition="The study of how stories are structured and how that structure creates meaning — applied here to system design" /></strong>. To me, code is not just a tool for computation—it is a medium for <em>structured intention</em>.
            </p>
          </span>
        </ShibuiContent>
        <button class="shibui-bridge" type="button">This section goes deeper</button>

        <ShibuiContent id="philosophy.thesis.p2">
          <span slot="entry">
            <p>I focus on making systems tell a coherent story — every part connected, every decision justified. I use AI to implement these designs with a thoroughness that's hard to achieve manually.</p>
          </span>
          <span slot="elevated">
            <p>
              As an <strong>AI-Native Architect</strong>, I focus on the <strong><ShibuiTerm term="Logocentric Architecture" definition="A design philosophy where narrative coherence and logical integrity govern every system decision" /></strong>: the narrative coherence and logical integrity of the system. I direct AI to implement these structures with a rigor that manual coding often misses.
            </p>
          </span>
        </ShibuiContent>
        <button class="shibui-bridge" type="button">This section goes deeper</button>

        <ShibuiContent id="philosophy.thesis.p3">
          <span slot="entry">
            <p>Most systems break not because of bad code, but because they lack a clear through-line. When the logic doesn't hang together, bugs multiply. When the design doesn't account for growth, it collapses.</p>
          </span>
          <span slot="elevated">
            <p>
              Most technical systems fail not because of bad syntax, but because of poor <strong><ShibuiTerm term="narrative coherence" definition="The quality of a system where every component's purpose is legible and its relationship to the whole is clear" /></strong>. If a system's <ShibuiTerm term="state machine" definition="A model describing all possible states a system can be in and the transitions between them" /> doesn't have a clear "character arc," it becomes buggy. If an orchestration layer lacks "rhetorical awareness," it collapses under scale.
            </p>
          </span>
        </ShibuiContent>
        <button class="shibui-bridge" type="button">This section goes deeper</button>

        <blockquote>
          "Humanities provide the 'Why' and the 'How things mean.' Engineering provides the 'What' and the 'How things work.' My work is the bridge."
        </blockquote>
      </section>

      <section class="ontology-mapping" data-reveal style="--stagger-index: 2">
        <h2 class="section-label">The Ontology: From Theory to Proof</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">Here is the exhaustive proof of how my academic background translates into technical qualification.</p>
        
        <div class="mapping-grid">
          {mappings.map((m) => (
            <div class="mapping-card">
              <div class="mapping-card__humanities">
                <span class="label">Humanities Concept</span>
                <h3>{m.humanities_concept}</h3>
              </div>
              <div class="mapping-card__arrow">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"></line><polyline points="12 5 19 12 12 19"></polyline></svg>
              </div>
              <div class="mapping-card__technical">
                <span class="label">Technical Abstraction</span>
                <h3>{m.technical_abstraction}</h3>
              </div>
              <div class="mapping-card__proof">
                <p><strong>The Proof:</strong> {m.proof}</p>
                <div class="mapping-card__tag">Implemented in: <code>{m.implementation}</code></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="identity-stack" data-reveal style="--stagger-index: 3">
        <h2 class="section-label">The Evolutionary Stack</h2>
        <ShibuiContent id="philosophy.stack.overview">
          <span slot="entry">
            <p>My path to technology wasn't a straight line — it was four distinct phases, each one building on the last. Literature taught me to read systems. Writing taught me to build them. Teaching taught me to explain them. Now I combine all three.</p>
          </span>
          <span slot="elevated">
            <p>
              The trajectory below is not a career pivot — it is a <ShibuiTerm term="recursive synthesis" definition="A process where each stage incorporates and transcends the previous, producing emergent capability at each iteration" />. Each phase supplied a cognitive tool that became load-bearing in the next.
            </p>
          </span>
        </ShibuiContent>
        <button class="shibui-bridge" type="button">This section goes deeper</button>

        <div class="timeline">
          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <h4>The Foundation: Undergraduate Literature</h4>
              <p>Critical analysis of complex texts. Learned to deconstruct systems of meaning before I ever touched a compiler.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <h4>The Craft: MFA in Creative Writing</h4>
              <p>Mastered the architecture of narrative and the rigor of peer review. Narrative design is the ultimate preparation for UX and system state machines.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <h4>The Praxis: A Decade in Postsecondary Education</h4>
              <p>Managed the "user experience" of learning for 2,000+ students. Learned to translate complex abstractions into clear, actionable protocols.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-item highlight">
            <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <h4>The Synthesis: The Eight-Organ System</h4>
              <p>The culmination of these identities. {vitals.repos.total} repositories of code, {wordsK}K words of documentation, and a fully governed creative ecosystem.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <footer class="philosophy-footer" data-reveal style="--stagger-index: 4">
        <h3>Ready to build something momentous?</h3>
        <p>Whether you need an AI Architect, a Creative Technologist, or a Strategic Lead, I bring a unique "Logocentric" edge to your team.</p>
        <div class="cta-group">
          <a href={`${base}resume/`} class="btn">View Specialized Resumes</a>
          <a href={`${base}consult/`} class="btn secondary">Inquire for Collaboration</a>
        </div>
      </footer>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .philosophy-page {
    padding: var(--space-3xl) 0;
  }

  .philosophy-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4xl);
  }

  .philosophy-subtitle {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .section-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    padding-left: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .section-intro {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  /* Ontology Mapping */
  .mapping-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4xl);
  }

  .mapping-card {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr;
    grid-template-areas: "hum arrow tech" "proof proof proof";
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    transition: border-color var(--transition-fast);
  }

  .mapping-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
  }

  .mapping-card__humanities { grid-area: hum; }
  .mapping-card__technical { grid-area: tech; }
  .mapping-card__arrow { 
    grid-area: arrow; 
    display: flex; 
    align-items: center; 
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .mapping-card__proof { 
    grid-area: proof;
    padding-top: var(--space-lg);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .mapping-card .label {
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .mapping-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .mapping-card__tag {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .mapping-card__tag code {
    color: var(--accent-text);
  }

  /* Timeline */
  .timeline {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4xl);
  }

  .timeline::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    width: 2px;
    background: var(--border);
  }

  .timeline-item {
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .timeline-marker {
    position: absolute;
    left: calc(-1 * var(--space-xl) - 5px);
    top: 0.5rem;
    width: 12px;
    height: 12px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--border);
    border: 2px solid var(--bg-primary);
  }

  .timeline-item.highlight .timeline-marker {
    background: var(--accent);
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--accent);
  }

  .timeline-content h4 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
    color: var(--accent-text);
  }

  /* Footer */
  .philosophy-footer {
    text-align: center;
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    padding: var(--space-3xl);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .philosophy-footer h3 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .cta-group {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .btn {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: var(--bg-primary);
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-xl);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 700;
    transition: transform 0.2s;
  }

  .btn.secondary {
    background: transparent;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .btn:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .mapping-card {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      grid-template-areas: "hum" "arrow" "tech" "proof";
    }
    .mapping-card__arrow {
      transform: rotate(90deg);
      justify-content: center;
    }
    .cta-group {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
  }
</style>
